EVPP 536: The Diversity of Fishes. 3 credits.
This course delves into the biology and ecology of fishes. Subjects of this class include fish anatomy, taxonomy, evolution, habitat adaptations, community dynamics, and ecosystem interactions. The course will also touch on human impacts on fishes, and conservation. Offered by Environmental Science & Policy. May not be repeated for credit.
