Grading: This course is graded on the Graduate Regular scale.

EVPP 610: Bioremediation: Theory and Applications. 3 credits.
Provides basis for understanding proper application of bioremedial technologies to treatment of hazardous wastes. Includes evaluation of data to determine successful treatment. Offered by Environmental Science & Policy. May not be repeated for credit. Equivalent to BIOL 610.
