EVPP 623: Translating Environmental Policy into Action. 3 credits.
Guest lecturers, class discussions, written and orally presented case studies, and assigned reading to identify and analyze factors involved in moving from science and policy to concrete action. Provides understanding of basic principles, skills, and strategies. Offered by Environmental Science & Policy. May not be repeated for credit.
