EVPP 630: Methods and Logic of Social Inquiry. 3 credits.
Emphasizes gathering, interpretation, and evaluation of scientific evidence. Develops critical thinking skills and covers logic of scientific inquiry, including various data collection methods such as experiments, observational research, and Q methodology. Offered by Environmental Science & Policy. May not be repeated for credit.
Recommended Prerequisite: An undergraduate course in statistics and research methods or Permission of Instructor.
