Grading: This course is graded on the Graduate Regular scale.

EVPP 670: Environmental Law. 3 credits.
Studies environmental laws such as the National Environmental Policy Act, and regulatory issues such as the Clean Water and Clean Air Acts. Emphasizes critical evaluation of alternatives to unresolved issues in environmental policies. Offered by Environmental Science & Policy. May not be repeated for credit.
