EVPP 675: Environmental Planning and Administration. 3 credits.
Examines interaction of man and ecological systems; causes of damage or deterioration in environment; content, oversights, and externalities in management decision processes that affect environment and effectiveness of plan implementation; means of assessing environmental impact; and administrative approaches for minimizing environmental impact. Offered by Environmental Science & Policy. May not be repeated for credit.
